<ns1760:section xmlns:ns1760="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.tecnologies.java.j2se.java2D.java2DImageProcessing.blurringImages">
    
    <ns1761:title xmlns:ns1761="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Blurring Images</ns1761:title>

<ns1762:para xmlns:ns1762="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Blurring is accomplished by averaging over surrounding pixels. The simplest
is to use the following convolution matrix
<ns1763:literal xmlns:ns1763="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
\[
  \left[ \begin{array}{ccc} \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} \\
                            \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} \\
                            \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} &amp; \frac{1}{9} 
  \end{array} \right]
\]                              
</ns1763:literal>
</ns1762:para>
<ns1764:para xmlns:ns1764="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The elements of a convolution matrix have to add to one if the image intensity
is to be preserved. </ns1764:para>
    
</ns1760:section>